D1 = property.getNumber("Default Code D1") D2 = property.getNumber("Default Code D2") D3 = property.getNumber("Default Code D3") D4 = property.getNumber("Default Code D4") SetD1 = false RStD1 = false InpD1 = -1 SetD2 = false RStD2 = false InpD2 = -1 SetD3 = false RStD3 = false InpD3 = -1 SetD4 = false RStD4 = false InpD4 = -1
BFR = 0 --Button fill colors BFG = 50 BFB = 255 BPR = 0 --Button press colors BPG = 150 BPB = 255
function onTick() inputX = input.getNumber(3) inputY = input.getNumber(4)
tch = input.getBool(1)
PB0 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 18-1,22-1,6+1,7+1) PB1 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 0-1,22-1,6+1,7+1) PB2 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 6-1,22-1,6+1,7+1) PB3 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 12-1,22-1,6+1,7+1) PB4 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 0-1,15-1,6+1,7+1) PB5 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 6-1,15-1,6+1,7+1) PB6 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 12-1,15-1,6+1,7+1) PB7 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 0-1,8-1,6+1,7+1) PB8 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 6-1,8-1,6+1,7+1) PB9 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 12-1,8-1,6+1,7+1)
PBE = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 18-1,8-1,6+1,7+1) PBR = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 18-1,15-1,6+1,7+1)
output.setBool(1, SetD1) output.setBool(11, RStD1) output.setNumber(1, InpD1) output.setBool(2, SetD2) output.setBool(12, RStD2) output.setNumber(2, InpD2) output.setBool(3, SetD3) output.setBool(13, RStD3) output.setNumber(3, InpD3) output.setBool(4, SetD4) output.setBool(14, RStD4) output.setNumber(4, InpD4) output.setBool(5, Accept)
i1 = input.getNumber(5) i2 = input.getNumber(6) i3 = input.getNumber(7) i4 = input.getNumber(8) c1 = input.getBool(4) c2 = input.getBool(5) c3 = input.getBool(6) c4 = input.getBool(7)
if i1>=0 and i2>=0 and i3>=0 and i4>=0 and i1==D1 and i2==D2 and i3==D3 and i4==D4 and PBE then Accept = true else Accept = false end
if i1==-1 then if PB0 then SetD1=true InpD1=0 elseif PB1 then SetD1=true InpD1=1 elseif PB2 then SetD1=true InpD1=2 elseif PB3 then SetD1=true InpD1=3 elseif PB4 then SetD1=true InpD1=4 elseif PB5 then SetD1=true InpD1=5 elseif PB6 then SetD1=true InpD1=6 elseif PB7 then SetD1=true InpD1=7 elseif PB8 then SetD1=true InpD1=8 elseif PB9 then SetD1=true InpD1=9 end else SetD1 = false InpD1=-1 end if i2==-1 and c1 then if PB0 then SetD2=true InpD2=0 elseif PB1 then SetD2=true InpD2=1 elseif PB2 then SetD2=true InpD2=2 elseif PB3 then SetD2=true InpD2=3 elseif PB4 then SetD2=true InpD2=4 elseif PB5 then SetD2=true InpD2=5 elseif PB6 then SetD2=true InpD2=6 elseif PB7 then SetD2=true InpD2=7 elseif PB8 then SetD2=true InpD2=8 elseif PB9 then SetD2=true InpD2=9 end else SetD2 = false InpD2=-1 end if i3==-1 and c2 then if PB0 then SetD3=true InpD3=0 elseif PB1 then SetD3=true InpD3=1 elseif PB2 then SetD3=true InpD3=2 elseif PB3 then SetD3=true InpD3=3 elseif PB4 then SetD3=true InpD3=4 elseif PB5 then SetD3=true InpD3=5 elseif PB6 then SetD3=true InpD3=6 elseif PB7 then SetD3=true InpD3=7 elseif PB8 then SetD3=true InpD3=8 elseif PB9 then SetD3=true InpD3=9 end else SetD3 = false InpD3=-1 end if i4==-1 and c3 then if PB0 then SetD4=true InpD4=0 elseif PB1 then SetD4=true InpD4=1 elseif PB2 then SetD4=true InpD4=2 elseif PB3 then SetD4=true InpD4=3 elseif PB4 then SetD4=true InpD4=4 elseif PB5 then SetD4=true InpD4=5 elseif PB6 then SetD4=true InpD4=6 elseif PB7 then SetD4=true InpD4=7 elseif PB8 then SetD4=true InpD4=8 elseif PB9 then SetD4=true InpD4=9 end else SetD4 = false InpD4=-1 end if i1>=0 then SetDx = SetD2 InpDx = InpD2 elseif i2>=0 then SetDx = SetD3 InpDx = InpD3 elseif i3>=0 then SetDx = SetD4 InpDx = InpD4 elseif i4>=0 then SetDx = SetD99 InpDx = InpD99 else SetDx = SetD1 InpDx = InpD1 end end
function TTarget(x, y, rectX, rectY, rectW, rectH) return x > rectX and y > rectY and x < rectX+rectW and y < rectY+rectH end

tch = input.getBool(1)
i1 = input.getNumber(5) i2 = input.getNumber(6) i3 = input.getNumber(7) i4 = input.getNumber(8)
PB0 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 18-1,22-1,6+1,7+1) PB1 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 0-1,22-1,6+1,7+1) PB2 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 6-1,22-1,6+1,7+1) PB3 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 12-1,22-1,6+1,7+1) PB4 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 0-1,15-1,6+1,7+1) PB5 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 6-1,15-1,6+1,7+1) PB6 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 12-1,15-1,6+1,7+1) PB7 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 0-1,8-1,6+1,7+1) PB8 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 6-1,8-1,6+1,7+1) PB9 = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 12-1,8-1,6+1,7+1)
PBE = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 18-1,8-1,6+1,7+1) PBR = tch and TTarget(inputX, inputY, 18-1,15-1,6+1,7+1)
if i1>=0 and i2==-1 then Asrk = "*" elseif i2>=0 and i3==-1 then Asrk = "**" elseif i3>=0 and i4==-1 then Asrk = "***" elseif i4>=0 then Asrk = "****" else Asrk = "" end
if i1>=0 and i2>=0 and i3>=0 and i4>=0 and i1==D1 and i2==D2 and i3==D3 and i4==D4 and PBE then CBR=0 CBG=255 CBB=0 elseif PBE then CBR=255 CBG=0 CBB=0 else CBR=0 CBG=25 CBB=100 end end

if PB0 then screen.setColor(BPR,BPG,BPB) else screen.setColor(BFR,BFG,BFB) end screen.drawRectF(18,22,6,7) if PB1 then screen.setColor(BPR,BPG,BPB) else screen.setColor(BFR,BFG,BFB) end screen.drawRectF(0,22,6,7) if PB2 then screen.setColor(BPR,BPG,BPB) else screen.setColor(BFR,BFG,BFB) end screen.drawRectF(6,22,6,7) if PB3 then screen.setColor(BPR,BPG,BPB) else screen.setColor(BFR,BFG,BFB) end screen.drawRectF(12,22,6,7) if PB4 then screen.setColor(BPR,BPG,BPB) else screen.setColor(BFR,BFG,BFB) end screen.drawRectF(0,15,6,7) if PB5 then screen.setColor(BPR,BPG,BPB) else screen.setColor(BFR,BFG,BFB) end screen.drawRectF(6,15,6,7) if PB6 then screen.setColor(BPR,BPG,BPB) else screen.setColor(BFR,BFG,BFB) end screen.drawRectF(12,15,6,7) if PB7 then screen.setColor(BPR,BPG,BPB) else screen.setColor(BFR,BFG,BFB) end screen.drawRectF(0,8,6,7) if PB8 then screen.setColor(BPR,BPG,BPB) else screen.setColor(BFR,BFG,BFB) end screen.drawRectF(6,8,6,7) if PB9 then screen.setColor(BPR,BPG,BPB) else screen.setColor(BFR,BFG,BFB) end screen.drawRectF(12,8,6,7)
if PBE then screen.setColor(50,255,50) else screen.setColor(0,50,0) end screen.drawRectF(18,8,6,7) if PBR then screen.setColor(255,50,50) else screen.setColor(50,0,0) end screen.drawRectF(18,15,6,7)
screen.setColor(255,255,255) screen.drawText(18+1,22+1,"0") screen.drawText(0+1,22+1,"1") screen.drawText(6+1,22+1,"2") screen.drawText(12+1,22+1,"3") screen.drawText(0+1,15+1,"4") screen.drawText(6+1,15+1,"5") screen.drawText(12+1,15+1,"6") screen.drawText(0+1,8+1,"7") screen.drawText(6+1,8+1,"8") screen.drawText(12+1,8+1,"9") screen.drawText(2,1, Asrk)
screen.drawText(18+1,8+1,"E") screen.drawText(18+1,15+1,"R") end

object.script:
targets = {} --creates table to store radar targets targetstime = {} pi = math.pi --shorthand for math.pi
function onTick()
BR = property.getNumber("BackroundR") BG = property.getNumber("BackroundG") BB = property.getNumber("BackroundB") TR = property.getNumber("TextR") TG = property.getNumber("TextG") TB = property.getNumber("TextB") TGTR = property.getNumber("TargetR") TGTG = property.getNumber("TargetG") TGTB = property.getNumber("TargetB")
w = input.getNumber(2) --user defined screen width h = input.getNumber(3) --user defined screen hieght r = h/2 --screen radius c1 = (r/5)*1 --screen radius c2 = (r/5)*2 --screen radius c3 = (r/5)*3 --screen radius c4 = (r/5)*4 --screen radius
t = input.getBool(11) --target is detected d = input.getNumber(6) --distane of target rg = input.getNumber(7) --desired radar range dad = (d/rg)*r --distance/max*radius on = input.getBool(1) --radar on or off rdrspd = (100 - input.getNumber(10)) * 6
radarrot = input.getNumber(8) --radar rotation
if on then --only turns and detects if radar is on
angrdr = radarrot*6.2832
x1 = w/2 + r * math.cos(angrdr-1.5708) --finds point to draw radar that rotates y1 = h/2 + r * math.sin(angrdr-1.5708)
x10 = w/2 + r * math.cos(angrdr-1.74533) --finds point to draw radar that rotates (Shadow 1) y10 = h/2 + r * math.sin(angrdr-1.74533)
x11 = w/2 + r * math.cos(angrdr-1.91986) --finds point to draw radar that rotates (Shadow 2) y11 = h/2 + r * math.sin(angrdr-1.91986)
x3 = w/2 + dad * math.cos(angrdr-1.5708) --finds point to draw radar target y3 = h/2 + dad * math.sin(angrdr-1.5708)
if t then --adds targets to table for each target found if d <= rg then time = 0 targets[x3] = y3 --stores x and y points in table targetstime[x3] = time --stores x and y points in table end end
for x3,time in pairs(targetstime) do targetstime[x3] = time + 1 if time >= rdrspd then targets[x3] = nil targetstime[x3] = nil end end
end end
function onDraw()
screen.setColor(BR, BG, BB) screen.drawClear()
screen.setColor(TR, TG, TB) --sets screen color to green screen.drawCircle(w/2, h/2, r) --draws a outside circle the size of the screen screen.setColor(TR, TG, TB, 30) --sets screen color to green screen.drawCircle(w/2, h/2, c1) --draws a circle 1 the size of the screen screen.drawCircle(w/2, h/2, c2) --draws a circle 2 the size of the screen screen.drawCircle(w/2, h/2, c3) --draws a circle 3 the size of the screen screen.drawCircle(w/2, h/2, c4) --draws a circle 4 the size of the screen
screen.drawLine(w/2-r, h/2, w/2+r, h/2) --draws the line left to right screen.drawLine(w/2, h/2-r, w/2, h/2+r) --draws the line top to bottom
screen.setColor(TR, TG, TB) --sets screen color to green screen.drawTextBox(1, 1, 20, 8, string.format("%#0d",rg), -1, -1) --displays the max range of radar screen.drawLine(w/2, h/2, x1, y1) --draws the line of radar that rotates
screen.setColor(TR, TG, TB, 150) --sets screen color to green (Shadow 1) screen.drawTriangleF(w/2, h/2, x10, y10, x1, y1) --draws the line of radar that rotates
screen.setColor(TR, TG, TB, 100) --sets screen color to green (Shadow 2) screen.drawTriangleF(w/2, h/2, x10, y10, x11, y11) --draws the line of radar that rotates
for x4, y4 in pairs(targets) do --reads the table of targets screen.setColor(TGTR, TGTG, TGTB) --sets the screen color to red screen.drawCircleF(x4,y4,1) --draws a dot/circle at target location on radar end end
